Hip_Hop vs.Â Country

Step 0. install and load needed libraries

Step 1. Load the dataset lyrics.RData and generate needed subsets

Get 3 subsets from the file:

  1. new.RData - contains both genres, hiphop and country
  2. hiphop.RData - contains genre hiphop only
  3. country.RData - contains genre country only

Step 2. Clean data

(Codes from the given Text_Processing.Rmd)

Clean the text by converting all the letters to the lower case, and removing punctuation, numbers, empty words and extra white space, and stem words then generate the corpuses.

Step 3. Transform corpuses to term document matrix.

Codes from the given InteractiveWordCloud.Rmd

Sava the tdm file as RData

Step 4. Compare bar charts of the top 10 frequent words in hiphop and country lyrics

Code from STHDA

We can see that âloveâ and âtimeâ are frequently used in both hiphop and country musics. However, by observing the words, the basic tones of two genres seems to be different.

Step.6 Sentiment Analysis

Code from Brian Ward

After observing the frequency chart and word cloud, we expect that the sentiment of Hophop is more negative than of Countrys. Letâs do the sentiment analysis and have a look of the scores.

In this step we get the summaries and plots of sentimentGI scores, also top 5 and bottom 5 songs for both genre by the score.

The mean and median of the Hiphop sentimentGI score are both negative, which indicates that overall itâs negative.

Step.7 Emotions Analysis

Code from Brian Ward

In this step we compare the distributions of emotions of hiphop and country lyrics by generating the bar chart.

We can see that other than âpositiveâ and ânegativeâ, the most frequently used emotion of hiphop is âfearâ whereas for country is âjoyâ. which is consistent with our guess again.

Step.8 Topic Modeling

code from Tutorial(Week 2) and tidytextmining

The goal is to make a heat map to see if Hiphop and Country lyrics share similar topics.

The dataset used in this step is new.RData. Use method and set k = 5 to get 5 topics from the hiphop and coutry lyrics. First convert the corpus to document term matrix. Then use LDA to get the topics and the terms in each topic by beta value. Then clustering the data frame and make the heat map.

Conclusion

By observing the word frequency, word cloud, sentimentGI score, emotions distribution and the topics analysis, we can conclude that Hip-hop and Country music lyrics are significantly different.

Hip-hop lyrics tend to be more negative. The words associated with âfearâ are used frequently. Whereas Country lyrics are more warm and positive. The words associated with âjoyâ are used frequently.

Eventhough two genresâ lyrics give different feeling, âLoveâ is the most popular theme for both.

This conclusion also consistent with our guess by the definitions and cultures.
